    "β = 3/4 Sect. 2.9.2.",
    "The error bars of these measurements, were too large to rule out alternative disc models.",
    "Thanks to multi-epoch data gathered for a sample of 11 systems, Morgan et al. (2010) alerted that, even if the size of the disc increased as M 2/3 BH, in agreement with the thindisc model, their too large absolute sizes implied thermal slopes in conflict with that model.",
    "The results from Blackburne et al. (2011), who used single-epoch multi-band data from X-ray to NIR for 12 lensed quasar systems, are in agreement with Morgan et al. (2010).",
